column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Cloudy , No Precipitation ,
column13: Ice at control feature with rotting ice in gauge pool. Suspect some flows are occuring during the daytime with warmer temps on site.
column14: Zero flow at beginning of site visit. Upgrades & programming done to logger, flow begins towards end of visit. Good quality Flowtracker2 measurements (given conditions) collected at the control feature. Minimum spacing encountered due to small contriction in channel where measurable flow was located. One reverse panel shot on the left bank. No significant QA/QC issues to note. @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ Float found pinned on arrival, beads are in float, lowered float to top of ice (@09:25:00) and not reset in order to maintain relationship set during the close-up visit. Ice in stilling well therefore ECG reading is invalid. ECG reading collected from top of ice. Secondary confirmatory water level conducted to validate SRC found to OTT. SRC found to OTT after reset, OTT appears to be slightly frozen - lower intake where OTT is strapped to (underside of intake) is partially visible with pooling of water around lower intake. Flow begins toward end of visit, suspect reciprocal SRC found as water level in gauge pool rises pushing ice cover up and lower intake where OTT is strapped to. Suspect lower intake where OTT is strapped to shifted during the influx of flow during visit. Stilling well is filling with water during measurement - suspended float on water's surface. Amasser set to outside DWL just prior to starting the wading measurement. WLs applied for before and after measurement to calculate MGH. Mid-section
